WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.465 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:02.465 --> 00:00:11.339 align:middle line:90%


00:00:11.339 --> 00:00:12.325 align:middle line:90%
>> Game over, man!

00:00:12.325 --> 00:00:13.830 align:middle line:90%
This is game over!

00:00:13.830 --> 00:00:16.620 align:middle line:84%
>> Bill Paxton was a star of
some of the biggest Hollywood

00:00:16.620 --> 00:00:19.147 align:middle line:84%
blockbusters of
the 1980s and '90s.

00:00:19.147 --> 00:00:20.480 align:middle line:90%
>> Three hours by the checklist.

00:00:20.480 --> 00:00:21.740 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS]

00:00:21.740 --> 00:00:24.990 align:middle line:10%
>> His illustrious career
beginning with character roles

00:00:24.990 --> 00:00:26.200 align:middle line:10%
in smash hit movies.

00:00:26.200 --> 00:00:30.600 align:middle line:90%


00:00:30.600 --> 00:00:43.350 align:middle line:84%
>> After filming people under
deep hypnosis for a decade,

00:00:43.350 --> 00:00:47.060 align:middle line:84%
I wondered if it is possible
to continue a conversation with

00:00:47.060 --> 00:00:49.210 align:middle line:84%
a loved one who
has crossed over.

00:00:49.210 --> 00:01:01.990 align:middle line:90%


00:01:01.990 --> 00:01:05.080 align:middle line:10%
Jennifer Shaffer is a medium
who works with law enforcement

00:01:05.080 --> 00:01:08.512 align:middle line:10%
agencies nationwide on
missing person cases.

00:01:08.512 --> 00:01:22.925 align:middle line:90%


00:01:22.925 --> 00:01:25.161 align:middle line:10%
I thought perhaps
her talents would

00:01:25.161 --> 00:01:28.889 align:middle line:10%
work with people I knew who
are no longer on the planet.

00:01:28.889 --> 00:01:42.380 align:middle line:90%


00:01:42.380 --> 00:01:45.978 align:middle line:10%
What if our loved ones
could still reach out to us?

00:01:45.978 --> 00:01:46.976 align:middle line:10%
What would we ask them?

00:01:46.976 --> 00:01:54.960 align:middle line:90%


00:01:54.960 --> 00:01:59.451 align:middle line:10%
Everything you're about to see
and hear was recorded verbatim.

00:01:59.451 --> 00:02:07.934 align:middle line:90%


00:02:07.934 --> 00:02:11.922 align:middle line:84%
"Backstage Pass to the Flipside:
Talking to Bill Paxton."

00:02:11.922 --> 00:02:17.230 align:middle line:90%


00:02:17.230 --> 00:02:19.540 align:middle line:10%
Written and directed
by Richard Martini.

00:02:19.540 --> 00:02:27.160 align:middle line:90%


00:02:27.160 --> 00:02:28.480 align:middle line:90%
Can we access Luana?

00:02:28.480 --> 00:02:30.310 align:middle line:90%
Can she come forward?

00:02:30.310 --> 00:02:31.110 align:middle line:90%
>> She's here.

00:02:31.110 --> 00:02:31.950 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:02:31.950 --> 00:02:32.365 align:middle line:90%
And so--

00:02:32.365 --> 00:02:33.990 align:middle line:90%
>> She's beautiful, by the way.

00:02:33.990 --> 00:02:37.330 align:middle line:84%
>> What is it that Luana
would like to tell us or say?

00:02:37.330 --> 00:02:40.430 align:middle line:84%
Or what's her amusing
thing for the day?

00:02:40.430 --> 00:02:43.034 align:middle line:90%


00:02:43.034 --> 00:02:44.030 align:middle line:10%
>> OK.

00:02:44.030 --> 00:02:44.970 align:middle line:10%
Hold on.

00:02:44.970 --> 00:02:47.008 align:middle line:84%
She says you're
doing everything.

00:02:47.008 --> 00:02:49.760 align:middle line:90%


00:02:49.760 --> 00:02:52.616 align:middle line:84%
And she says you're
doing everything right.

00:02:52.616 --> 00:02:55.260 align:middle line:84%
But you-- then she
showed me like a stop,

00:02:55.260 --> 00:02:56.550 align:middle line:90%
like you stopped yourself.

00:02:56.550 --> 00:02:58.930 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:58.930 --> 00:03:02.420 align:middle line:90%


00:03:02.420 --> 00:03:03.220 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:03:03.220 --> 00:03:05.597 align:middle line:84%
So she's showing
you in the center.

00:03:05.597 --> 00:03:07.180 align:middle line:84%
She's saying that
you stopped yourself

00:03:07.180 --> 00:03:09.810 align:middle line:84%
from being vulnerable
because-- and then

00:03:09.810 --> 00:03:12.730 align:middle line:84%
she showed me all the people
that have passed around you.

00:03:12.730 --> 00:03:15.640 align:middle line:90%
And believe me, I've only had--

00:03:15.640 --> 00:03:18.510 align:middle line:84%
I've had a few people that have
passed, but nothing like this.

00:03:18.510 --> 00:03:22.130 align:middle line:10%
>> And in reference to what
Luana's saying about what--

00:03:22.130 --> 00:03:24.340 align:middle line:10%
is she saying stay more open?

00:03:24.340 --> 00:03:27.790 align:middle line:10%
>> She's saying, stay more
open and put your shields down.

00:03:27.790 --> 00:03:31.030 align:middle line:10%
>> Luana, while we're here, we
have a mutual friend who passed

00:03:31.030 --> 00:03:33.320 align:middle line:10%
away recently, Bill.

00:03:33.320 --> 00:03:34.225 align:middle line:10%
And is he avai--

00:03:34.225 --> 00:03:35.350 align:middle line:10%
does he want to talk to us?

00:03:35.350 --> 00:03:37.700 align:middle line:10%
>> [GASP] Oh, they just danced.

00:03:37.700 --> 00:03:38.500 align:middle line:90%
That's interesting.

00:03:38.500 --> 00:03:39.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Who's they?

00:03:39.640 --> 00:03:40.440 align:middle line:90%
>> Bill.

00:03:40.440 --> 00:03:41.590 align:middle line:90%
>> And?

00:03:41.590 --> 00:03:41.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Luana.

00:03:41.950 --> 00:03:42.750 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh.

00:03:42.750 --> 00:03:44.452 align:middle line:84%
>> They did like a
little tango thing.

00:03:44.452 --> 00:03:46.140 align:middle line:90%
It's kind of funny.

00:03:46.140 --> 00:03:49.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Does Bill want to talk to us?

00:03:49.170 --> 00:03:51.480 align:middle line:84%
So tell us what it's
like for you over there.

00:03:51.480 --> 00:03:53.680 align:middle line:90%
And who was the first person--

00:03:53.680 --> 00:03:54.660 align:middle line:90%
>> He says it's fun.

00:03:54.660 --> 00:03:56.505 align:middle line:90%
He's, like, scaring people.

00:03:56.505 --> 00:03:59.425 align:middle line:84%
>> Who was the first person
to greet you when you stepped

00:03:59.425 --> 00:03:59.630 align:middle line:90%
off--

00:03:59.630 --> 00:04:00.430 align:middle line:90%
>> His dad.

00:04:00.430 --> 00:04:01.800 align:middle line:90%
>> His dad, OK.

00:04:01.800 --> 00:04:05.280 align:middle line:84%
And was that a happy thing,
a happy connection, or?

00:04:05.280 --> 00:04:08.380 align:middle line:84%
>> Shocking, because
that meant he died.

00:04:08.380 --> 00:04:10.724 align:middle line:90%
So I just saw that, like--

00:04:10.724 --> 00:04:12.380 align:middle line:90%
hold on.

00:04:12.380 --> 00:04:17.850 align:middle line:84%
Billy's saying that, at
first, he was startled.

00:04:17.850 --> 00:04:19.352 align:middle line:90%
But it wasn't scary.

00:04:19.352 --> 00:04:20.810 align:middle line:84%
His heart didn't--
it wasn't scary.

00:04:20.810 --> 00:04:25.450 align:middle line:90%


00:04:25.450 --> 00:04:28.710 align:middle line:84%
He says it was like
recognition of both worlds.

00:04:28.710 --> 00:04:30.380 align:middle line:84%
That he's leaving
one, and then--

00:04:30.380 --> 00:04:32.620 align:middle line:84%
it shows them going
together as one.

00:04:32.620 --> 00:04:34.420 align:middle line:84%
>> Was this an
exit point for you?

00:04:34.420 --> 00:04:36.430 align:middle line:84%
Was this something
that you had planned

00:04:36.430 --> 00:04:38.306 align:middle line:90%
that maybe would happen?

00:04:38.306 --> 00:04:40.820 align:middle line:84%
Was this the right time,
or was this the wrong time?

00:04:40.820 --> 00:04:48.750 align:middle line:90%


00:04:48.750 --> 00:04:50.170 align:middle line:90%
>> His physical body was--

00:04:50.170 --> 00:04:54.380 align:middle line:84%
it was the wrong
time for him here.

00:04:54.380 --> 00:04:56.640 align:middle line:84%
It was the right
time for his soul.

00:04:56.640 --> 00:04:58.142 align:middle line:90%
>> I understand.

00:04:58.142 --> 00:05:00.420 align:middle line:84%
And let me ask you,
you talked about going

00:05:00.420 --> 00:05:02.867 align:middle line:90%
to visit the Titanic.

00:05:02.867 --> 00:05:04.950 align:middle line:84%
Would you describe what
that was like to Jennifer?

00:05:04.950 --> 00:05:08.310 align:middle line:90%


00:05:08.310 --> 00:05:10.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Is it the Billy
that was in the Tit--

00:05:10.800 --> 00:05:11.690 align:middle line:90%
no.

00:05:11.690 --> 00:05:12.777 align:middle line:90%
>> Ask him!

00:05:12.777 --> 00:05:15.360 align:middle line:84%
>> Because he just showed me a
picture of when you were saying

00:05:15.360 --> 00:05:17.040 align:middle line:84%
that of the guy that
recently passed.

00:05:17.040 --> 00:05:17.910 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:05:17.910 --> 00:05:21.000 align:middle line:90%
Is that-- ask him!

00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:24.020 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm so confused.

00:05:24.020 --> 00:05:25.030 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:05:25.030 --> 00:05:29.430 align:middle line:90%
>> Billy, is that picture you?

00:05:29.430 --> 00:05:31.130 align:middle line:84%
Give her a thumbs
up or a thumbs down.

00:05:31.130 --> 00:05:32.290 align:middle line:90%
>> He gave me a thumbs up.

00:05:32.290 --> 00:05:33.280 align:middle line:90%
>> OK, very good.

00:05:33.280 --> 00:05:34.080 align:middle line:90%
Yes, that's him.

00:05:34.080 --> 00:05:35.025 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh my gosh.

00:05:35.025 --> 00:05:36.400 align:middle line:84%
Well, he was there
the other day.

00:05:36.400 --> 00:05:37.805 align:middle line:90%
But he had blond--

00:05:37.805 --> 00:05:41.970 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, he grew up as a blondie
from Texas and his hair got

00:05:41.970 --> 00:05:42.770 align:middle line:90%
browner.

00:05:42.770 --> 00:05:44.353 align:middle line:84%
And it was dyed by
the time he passed.

00:05:44.353 --> 00:05:45.510 align:middle line:90%
>> You confused me when--

00:05:45.510 --> 00:05:47.354 align:middle line:84%
and that's where I get
hung up, because I saw him,

00:05:47.354 --> 00:05:47.520 align:middle line:90%
but I didn't know--

00:05:47.520 --> 00:05:49.380 align:middle line:84%
>> No, I don't know if
his hair was ever blond.

00:05:49.380 --> 00:05:50.020 align:middle line:90%
I really don't know.

00:05:50.020 --> 00:05:50.320 align:middle line:90%
Maybe that's his--

00:05:50.320 --> 00:05:51.480 align:middle line:84%
>> No blond, but
it was just dirty.

00:05:51.480 --> 00:05:53.055 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, but that's maybe the
way he wants to look between

00:05:53.055 --> 00:05:53.855 align:middle line:90%
lives.

00:05:53.855 --> 00:05:54.930 align:middle line:90%
>> No, I love Billy!

00:05:54.930 --> 00:05:55.730 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:05:55.730 --> 00:05:56.530 align:middle line:90%
>> I love Billy.

00:05:56.530 --> 00:05:58.050 align:middle line:90%
I had no i--

00:05:58.050 --> 00:05:59.520 align:middle line:90%
>> I wanted you to say it.

00:05:59.520 --> 00:06:00.610 align:middle line:90%
I didn't want to say it.

00:06:00.610 --> 00:06:03.095 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:03.095 --> 00:06:23.969 align:middle line:90%


00:06:23.969 --> 00:06:24.963 align:middle line:90%
>> Shoot.

00:06:24.963 --> 00:06:25.957 align:middle line:90%
That was funny.

00:06:25.957 --> 00:06:28.970 align:middle line:90%
That was a shark.

00:06:28.970 --> 00:06:30.120 align:middle line:90%
>> Why was it a shark?

00:06:30.120 --> 00:06:31.320 align:middle line:90%
He showed you a shark, or--

00:06:31.320 --> 00:06:33.870 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, a shark swam by.

00:06:33.870 --> 00:06:35.850 align:middle line:90%
And I'm-- it's--

00:06:35.850 --> 00:06:36.650 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:06:36.650 --> 00:06:39.084 align:middle line:90%


00:06:39.084 --> 00:06:39.884 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLES]

00:06:39.884 --> 00:06:41.801 align:middle line:84%
He's like, you don't
have to hold your breath.

00:06:41.801 --> 00:06:45.254 align:middle line:90%
I started holding my breath.

00:06:45.254 --> 00:06:49.505 align:middle line:84%
>> So describe what you're
seeing and feeling, if you can.

00:06:49.505 --> 00:06:51.135 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm feeling a sense of peace.

00:06:51.135 --> 00:06:52.420 align:middle line:90%
It's so fine.

00:06:52.420 --> 00:06:53.526 align:middle line:90%
This is really fine.

00:06:53.526 --> 00:06:57.855 align:middle line:84%
>> So what does the
Titanic look like?

00:06:57.855 --> 00:07:01.760 align:middle line:84%
>> I would be really scared
to ever go into something like

00:07:01.760 --> 00:07:04.370 align:middle line:84%
that in any machine or
anything, even if it was safe.

00:07:04.370 --> 00:07:07.096 align:middle line:84%
I'd be very, very
scared because it--

00:07:07.096 --> 00:07:08.990 align:middle line:84%
they did a pretty
good job in the movie.

00:07:08.990 --> 00:07:10.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, he did it.

00:07:10.610 --> 00:07:12.440 align:middle line:84%
He went down there
with Jim Cameron

00:07:12.440 --> 00:07:14.090 align:middle line:90%
like four or five times.

00:07:14.090 --> 00:07:15.470 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow.

00:07:15.470 --> 00:07:16.860 align:middle line:90%
>> And he talked about it.

00:07:16.860 --> 00:07:19.340 align:middle line:84%
It was the most dramatic thing
he'd ever done in his life.

00:07:19.340 --> 00:07:21.980 align:middle line:84%
He thought he was just going to
go out there and be on the ship

00:07:21.980 --> 00:07:23.013 align:middle line:90%
when Jim came back up.

00:07:23.013 --> 00:07:24.680 align:middle line:84%
And Jim said, no,
you're coming with me.

00:07:24.680 --> 00:07:27.220 align:middle line:84%
And they went down in this tiny
bathysphere all the way down

00:07:27.220 --> 00:07:28.020 align:middle line:90%
to the ship.

00:07:28.020 --> 00:07:29.620 align:middle line:90%
And he did it like four times.

00:07:29.620 --> 00:07:33.180 align:middle line:90%
>> So for me, I'm afraid of--

00:07:33.180 --> 00:07:33.980 align:middle line:90%
he just showed me.

00:07:33.980 --> 00:07:36.050 align:middle line:84%
It's my past life
stuff that is causing

00:07:36.050 --> 00:07:37.490 align:middle line:90%
me to be afraid of the ocean.

00:07:37.490 --> 00:07:39.610 align:middle line:90%
That's funny in and of itself.

00:07:39.610 --> 00:07:44.950 align:middle line:84%
But he's taking me down
to the right of the bow.

00:07:44.950 --> 00:07:45.750 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:07:45.750 --> 00:07:47.430 align:middle line:90%
It's the right, but it's below.

00:07:47.430 --> 00:07:51.690 align:middle line:84%
It's on the bottom,
in the front.

00:07:51.690 --> 00:07:52.510 align:middle line:90%
And there's a hole.

00:07:52.510 --> 00:07:55.250 align:middle line:90%


00:07:55.250 --> 00:07:57.552 align:middle line:90%
There's a hole in the front.

00:07:57.552 --> 00:07:59.010 align:middle line:84%
And then he showed
me an explosion.

00:07:59.010 --> 00:08:03.070 align:middle line:84%
I believe one of
the explosions--

00:08:03.070 --> 00:08:05.400 align:middle line:84%
well, I don't know, but
he showed me an explosion

00:08:05.400 --> 00:08:06.640 align:middle line:90%
that caused that part--

00:08:06.640 --> 00:08:10.169 align:middle line:90%


00:08:10.169 --> 00:08:11.926 align:middle line:90%
it's in the front.

00:08:11.926 --> 00:08:13.220 align:middle line:90%
>> Very good.

00:08:13.220 --> 00:08:14.020 align:middle line:90%
Very good.

00:08:14.020 --> 00:08:15.850 align:middle line:84%
>> It's in the front,
what he showed me.

00:08:15.850 --> 00:08:19.230 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, that's where the--

00:08:19.230 --> 00:08:20.630 align:middle line:90%
supposedly, there was a fire.

00:08:20.630 --> 00:08:22.100 align:middle line:90%
Maybe it's possible.

00:08:22.100 --> 00:08:25.000 align:middle line:84%
But they hit the iceberg
on the right side, and--

00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:26.480 align:middle line:90%
>> I didn't know that.

00:08:26.480 --> 00:08:27.280 align:middle line:90%
I have no--

00:08:27.280 --> 00:08:29.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, I'm just--

00:08:29.640 --> 00:08:31.480 align:middle line:84%
but we're mostly about
connecting to Billy.

00:08:31.480 --> 00:08:33.380 align:middle line:10%
So I wanted him to
show that to you,

00:08:33.380 --> 00:08:35.648 align:middle line:10%
and what his experience
was like doing that.

00:08:35.648 --> 00:08:37.440 align:middle line:84%
>> He's making fun of
me decompressing now.

00:08:37.440 --> 00:08:39.030 align:middle line:90%
My whole face is like--

00:08:39.030 --> 00:08:41.644 align:middle line:90%


00:08:41.644 --> 00:08:43.039 align:middle line:90%
that's interesting.

00:08:43.039 --> 00:08:44.030 align:middle line:90%
>> Very good.

00:08:44.030 --> 00:08:45.530 align:middle line:84%
Now, we have some
mutual friends.

00:08:45.530 --> 00:08:46.805 align:middle line:90%
We have John and Lori.

00:08:46.805 --> 00:08:50.120 align:middle line:90%
I met Billy in a pub in London.

00:08:50.120 --> 00:08:53.810 align:middle line:84%
And he was dating his
girlfriend Louise.

00:08:53.810 --> 00:08:57.170 align:middle line:84%
He told me about her, and he
was doing that movie "Aliens."

00:08:57.170 --> 00:09:01.652 align:middle line:84%
And he laughed really loudly,
and I went, oh my god.

00:09:01.652 --> 00:09:03.680 align:middle line:84%
You're the guy who was
in "Weird Science."

00:09:03.680 --> 00:09:06.440 align:middle line:84%
Now, have you had a chance
to see John Hughes since you

00:09:06.440 --> 00:09:08.500 align:middle line:90%
got home, or is he--

00:09:08.500 --> 00:09:10.680 align:middle line:90%
>> He says he's really busy.

00:09:10.680 --> 00:09:11.490 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:09:11.490 --> 00:09:12.290 align:middle line:90%
Helping people out?

00:09:12.290 --> 00:09:13.090 align:middle line:90%
>> It's amazing.

00:09:13.090 --> 00:09:15.760 align:middle line:84%
You can always be
connected to us, but we--

00:09:15.760 --> 00:09:17.965 align:middle line:84%
but you guys are
really-- this is what--

00:09:17.965 --> 00:09:19.295 align:middle line:90%
he's saying, don't be confused.

00:09:19.295 --> 00:09:21.260 align:middle line:84%
He just went like
this to my head.

00:09:21.260 --> 00:09:22.060 align:middle line:90%
Stop that.

00:09:22.060 --> 00:09:23.630 align:middle line:90%
It's not very nice.

00:09:23.630 --> 00:09:24.440 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, hold on.

00:09:24.440 --> 00:09:27.840 align:middle line:84%
Will and I were going to make
a movie together in 1986.

00:09:27.840 --> 00:09:29.510 align:middle line:84%
And now this is our
chance, finally,

00:09:29.510 --> 00:09:30.860 align:middle line:90%
to make a film together.

00:09:30.860 --> 00:09:31.970 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:09:31.970 --> 00:09:33.740 align:middle line:84%
And that's why it's
important for you

00:09:33.740 --> 00:09:35.480 align:middle line:84%
to tell messages
to your friends,

00:09:35.480 --> 00:09:37.400 align:middle line:84%
because I will get
these messages.

00:09:37.400 --> 00:09:38.450 align:middle line:90%
So Jim Cameron.

00:09:38.450 --> 00:09:39.290 align:middle line:90%
Anything to Jim?

00:09:39.290 --> 00:09:42.242 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

