01:16:43.050 --> 01:16:47.280 align:middle line:10%
and was one of the best acting
roles that ever came down

01:16:47.280 --> 01:16:48.660 align:middle line:10%
the road for me.

01:16:48.660 --> 01:16:52.230 align:middle line:10%
And I wanted to get back
to doing that kind of work.

01:16:52.230 --> 01:16:53.970 align:middle line:10%
I like to kind of mix it up.

01:16:53.970 --> 01:16:56.910 align:middle line:10%
It's great to do the
big commercial films.

01:16:56.910 --> 01:17:00.450 align:middle line:10%
I wouldn't have been
able to raise the money

01:17:00.450 --> 01:17:04.680 align:middle line:10%
to finance "Traveller" if
it wasn't for "Twister."

01:17:04.680 --> 01:17:08.700 align:middle line:10%
And this was a script that
my wife found four years ago.

01:17:08.700 --> 01:17:12.810 align:middle line:10%
And "One False Move" was
a real departure for me.

01:17:12.810 --> 01:17:15.720 align:middle line:10%
It put me in a position with
a lot of serious filmmakers

01:17:15.720 --> 01:17:19.680 align:middle line:10%
in Hollywood, like Ron
Howard and [INAUDIBLE]..

01:17:19.680 --> 01:17:23.370 align:middle line:10%
This was the movie they saw, and
they saw me as a leading man.

01:17:23.370 --> 01:17:26.190 align:middle line:10%
Before that, I had done
some leads in some movies.

01:17:26.190 --> 01:17:29.070 align:middle line:10%
But for the most part, I was
known as a working character

01:17:29.070 --> 01:17:33.480 align:middle line:10%
actor doing parts in movies like
"Weird Science" and "Aliens"

01:17:33.480 --> 01:17:34.980 align:middle line:10%
and "True Lies."

01:17:34.980 --> 01:17:38.470 align:middle line:10%
So I saw a great opportunity.

01:17:38.470 --> 01:17:40.350 align:middle line:10%
I think you get to a
point in your career

01:17:40.350 --> 01:17:44.110 align:middle line:10%
where you really need to take
the reins and try to do--

01:17:44.110 --> 01:17:48.900 align:middle line:10%
and it's always been
my dream for 20 years

01:17:48.900 --> 01:17:50.970 align:middle line:10%
to produce a movie
that I could act in.

01:17:50.970 --> 01:17:54.930 align:middle line:10%
So I wanted to be involved in
the casting, in the director,

01:17:54.930 --> 01:17:58.250 align:middle line:10%
in the editing, in the
music, in the art direction.

01:17:58.250 --> 01:18:00.625 align:middle line:10%
I don't know who's seen it
the most times in here besides

01:18:00.625 --> 01:18:02.480 align:middle line:10%
probably me.

01:18:02.480 --> 01:18:03.312 align:middle line:10%
How many times?

01:18:03.312 --> 01:18:04.770 align:middle line:10%
>> Probably seen
it about 10 times.

01:18:04.770 --> 01:18:05.710 align:middle line:10%
>> Nice.

01:18:05.710 --> 01:18:06.528 align:middle line:10%
Nice.

01:18:06.528 --> 01:18:07.570 align:middle line:10%
Thanks for the residuals.

01:18:07.570 --> 01:18:08.370 align:middle line:10%
[LAUGHTER]

01:18:08.370 --> 01:18:10.860 align:middle line:10%
>> --sum up my
friendship with him.

01:18:10.860 --> 01:18:13.790 align:middle line:84%
In a soundbite, he
was a dear friend.

01:18:13.790 --> 01:18:15.040 align:middle line:10%
He was family, and--

01:18:15.040 --> 01:18:18.120 align:middle line:10%
yeah, I'm having--
it's been a hard day.

01:18:18.120 --> 01:18:21.220 align:middle line:10%
I thought about not coming,
and Josh reminded me

01:18:21.220 --> 01:18:24.400 align:middle line:10%
that Bill loves everything
Hollywood tradition, Hollywood

01:18:24.400 --> 01:18:25.870 align:middle line:10%
history, and he
would have kicked

01:18:25.870 --> 01:18:27.520 align:middle line:10%
my butt if I didn't come.

01:18:27.520 --> 01:18:30.760 align:middle line:84%
>> And he left behind such
a great body of work that,

01:18:30.760 --> 01:18:33.620 align:middle line:84%
whenever we're missing him or
we want to hang out with him,

01:18:33.620 --> 01:18:33.940 align:middle line:90%
we can.

01:18:33.940 --> 01:18:36.160 align:middle line:10%
>> Finally, tonight here,
with so much attention paid

01:18:36.160 --> 01:18:38.950 align:middle line:10%
to the Oscars, tonight we
celebrate one more Hollywood

01:18:38.950 --> 01:18:39.760 align:middle line:10%
favorite--

01:18:39.760 --> 01:18:40.810 align:middle line:10%
Bill Paxton.

01:18:40.810 --> 01:18:43.090 align:middle line:84%
He was in so many great
movies, and tonight, his fans,

01:18:43.090 --> 01:18:46.060 align:middle line:84%
his colleagues, Tom Hanks
all remembering him.

01:18:46.060 --> 01:18:47.542 align:middle line:90%
Here's Kayna Whitworth.

01:18:47.542 --> 01:18:50.180 align:middle line:84%
>> He was a Hollywood
favorite, and the world learned

01:18:50.180 --> 01:18:52.790 align:middle line:84%
of the loss just hours
before the Oscars.

01:18:52.790 --> 01:18:55.100 align:middle line:84%
>> Can you tell us who the
woman in the picture is?

01:18:55.100 --> 01:18:57.950 align:middle line:84%
>> Bill Paxton was a prolific
actor known for roles

01:18:57.950 --> 01:18:59.720 align:middle line:84%
in blockbuster movies
like "Titanic."

01:18:59.720 --> 01:19:00.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Tell us, Rose.

01:19:00.950 --> 01:19:02.895 align:middle line:10%
>> It's been 84 years.

01:19:02.895 --> 01:19:05.360 align:middle line:84%
>> One of Paxton's
first big breaks,

01:19:05.360 --> 01:19:08.240 align:middle line:84%
the obnoxious older brother
Chet in "Weird Science."

01:19:08.240 --> 01:19:11.180 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you realize it's
snowing in my room?

01:19:11.180 --> 01:19:12.710 align:middle line:10%
>> Then, "Aliens."

01:19:12.710 --> 01:19:13.856 align:middle line:10%
>> That's great.

01:19:13.856 --> 01:19:17.275 align:middle line:84%
>> And later, taking the
starring role in "Twister."

01:19:17.275 --> 01:19:19.466 align:middle line:90%
>> Tighten your seat belt.

01:19:19.466 --> 01:19:22.170 align:middle line:84%
>> One of his most
critically-acclaimed roles,

01:19:22.170 --> 01:19:23.160 align:middle line:90%
"Apollo 13."

01:19:23.160 --> 01:19:25.205 align:middle line:84%
>> Uh, Houston, we got a
pretty large bang there,

01:19:25.205 --> 01:19:26.580 align:middle line:84%
especially with
the master alarm.

01:19:26.580 --> 01:19:28.860 align:middle line:90%
>> Tributes now pouring in.

01:19:28.860 --> 01:19:31.110 align:middle line:10%
Co-star Tom Hanks
tweeting, "Bill Paxton

01:19:31.110 --> 01:19:33.600 align:middle line:10%
was simply a wonderful man."

01:19:33.600 --> 01:19:35.730 align:middle line:84%
The two also starring
in the upcoming movie

01:19:35.730 --> 01:19:39.630 align:middle line:84%
"The Circle," a film that's
now Paxton's final farewell

01:19:39.630 --> 01:19:41.010 align:middle line:90%
to Tinseltown.

